-- Belgian Trade Returns to Surplus in June After May Deficit
-- B y   A n d r e w   C l a p h a m
-- 2012-08-16T13:18:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/belgian-trade-returns-to-surplus-in-june-after-deficit-in-may.html
Belgium reported a  trade surplus  in
June as exports increased and imports fell.  The trade surplus of 655.2 million euros followed a revised
deficit of 139.1 million euros a month earlier, the  National
Bank of Belgium  said on its  website  today.  Exports rose 0.6 percent from the year-earlier period,
while imports declined 3.6 percent, according to an e-mailed
report. The central bank report previously reported a trade
surplus of 125.6 million euros in May.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Clapham in Brussels at 
